    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors achieve their required levels (requiredLevel 2, achievedLevel 2) for Model Risk Level 2 with a Class II CPB device. The six scoped-out factors are appropriately excluded at MRL 2 with documented rationale. The operating envelope is explicitly bounded (1–7 L/min, 1500–3500 RPM, ±0.05 mm geometric tolerances) and declared as an inline structured object. Validation coverage is concentrated in the central envelope region (2–5 L/min, 2000–3000 RPM) with sparse coverage at extremes; this gap is honestly documented in validation results VR-01 and VR-02 with widened uncertainty intervals at extremes rather than suppressed. Grid convergence is confirmed (GCI 2.3%). All three validation results carry comparedAgainst, prov:wasGeneratedBy, and hasUncertaintyQuantification links. The primary QoI (NIH, RH < 1.0) is directly linked to the regulatory decision criterion. The credibility evidence package is complete and internally consistent; acceptance is warranted for the stated COU.",
